   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER FOUR THE MIRACULOUSLY NORMAL LIVING IN THE NEW WAY Scripture Reading: Heb 7:25; Phil 1:19; 4:13; Heb 3:12 OUTLINE Being revived every morning: Calling on the Lord and contacting the Lord immediately upon rising up in the morning.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Enjoying the Lord and absorbing the Lord's rich supply using a few verses.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Living an overcoming life daily: Calling on the Lord unceasingly Rom 10:12.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Dealing with sins and being filled with the Spirit at all times.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Walking according to spirit Rom 8:4.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Living Christ Phil 1:21.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Speaking the Lord in any place at any time 2 Tim 4:2.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Gaining people by preaching the gospel: Going to visit people twice a month.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Going out two hours each time.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Perfecting the new believers: Setting up a meeting in new believers' homes Acts 2:46; 5:42.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Leading the new believers to go on in the spiritual life and to function in the meetings.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Leading a small number of believers: Setting up group meetings.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Leading the new believers to have contact and fellowship with neighboring saints in the group meetings.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Leading the new believers to go on further in functioning in the group meetings by speaking for the Lord.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Participating in the district meetings: Striving to speak for the Lord and speak forth the Lord 1 Cor 14:26, 31.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Exercising to be in the same flow and to coordinate with the saints in speaking for the Lord.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Supplying to perfect the saints, building up the Body of Christ Eph 4:12.</S>
   </TEXT>
